The paper proposes a compressive sensing-based differential channel feedback scheme for massive MIMO, which involves exploiting temporal correlation and sparsity of time-varying channels. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Signal Processing (cs.SI), Multimedia (cs.MM), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, given the focus on compressive sensing and its application to wireless communications, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible given the use of signal processing and machine learning techniques in the proposed scheme.
